Posts.Content: Aug 12, 2008 05:49AM mussylou wrote: Love this site myself.  I was Dx in May, had right breast removed in June, Started chemo in August.  Good days and bad days are to be expected.  I get my port put in today, veins not supporting the 8 treatments that I need.  After chemo...rads start.  Long process but this too I will get through.  It is great to read all others and how they are coping.  Good luck to all and Keep praying and let the Lord take your burdens.  Mussylou
Posts.Title: I just wanted to say thank you!!! Genia mussylou
